  "body": "I'm setting a `ref` on an element, but it doesn't show up. This is what I'm doing in a class:\n\n``` js\n    constructor(props) {\n        super(props)\n\n        this.bigGpsButtonElement = class extends Node {\n            render() {\n                return (\n                    <Button _famousParent={this} ref=\"bigGpsButton\"> </Button>\n                )\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    render() {\n        return (\n            <Node _famousParent={this}>\n                <this.bigGpsButtonElement ref=\"bigGpsButtonElement\" />\n            </Node>\n        )\n    }\n\n    componentDidMount() {\n        console.log('ref?', this.refs.bigGpsButtonElement) // Error\n    }\n```\n\nWhen the `console.log` statement fires, I get the error\n\n```\nUncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'refs' of undefined\n```\n\nWhy is that?\n",
